1
00:00:13,440 --> 00:00:16,399
We'd seized Baan Prongdong Base
for only a few days before it was overrun.

2
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:18,879
We can't even hold a base this small.

3
00:00:18,880 --> 00:00:20,960
So how are we supposed
to protect the whole country?

4
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:24,440
If we let this drag on, they'll
only grow more confident.

5
00:00:25,440 --> 00:00:27,720
How far have you gotten
inside their inner circle?

6
00:00:29,480 --> 00:00:30,920
I just need a little more time, sir.

7
00:00:32,280 --> 00:00:33,759
We're out of time!

8
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:36,999
Orders have come down that we must
take down the Baan Saeng Dao base.

9
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:39,640
This has dragged on far too long, Dan Din.

10
00:00:40,560 --> 00:00:43,199
But Baan Saeng Dao
base isn't just armed forces.

11
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:45,440
There are civilians in there too, sir.

12
00:00:47,440 --> 00:00:48,440
Dan Din.

13
00:00:49,840 --> 00:00:52,120
For the peace of the entire country,

14
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:55,680
we have to do things we don't want to do.

15
00:00:57,880 --> 00:00:59,480
But if you're not comfortable with this,

16
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:02,400
you can request a transfer back to Bangkok.

17
00:01:09,160 --> 00:01:10,279
In that case,

18
00:01:10,280 --> 00:01:12,561
I'll find a way to infiltrate
Baan Saeng Dao base myself.

19
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:03,000
"When Light Fades"
(Episode 4)

20
00:02:18,480 --> 00:02:19,960
Oh! Comrade Saeng.

21
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:22,400
Bai Tong.

22
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:25,799
You feeling better, Comrade Saeng?

23
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,240
You promised to teach us basketball.

24
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:30,239
I'm good now. Feeling great.

25
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,720
Let your arm heal first.

26
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:33,879
Don't overuse it yet.

27
00:02:33,880 --> 00:02:35,440
How are you doing, Comrade Saeng?

28
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,000
Thank you.

29
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:44,240
For helping us take Baan Prongdong back.

30
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:47,039
It's not just a victory,

31
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:50,519
but morale for all of us.

32
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:52,880
The main base sent their praise too.

33
00:02:58,560 --> 00:03:01,920
What's wrong, Comrade Saeng?
Why aren't you smiling?

34
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:05,840
I just can't.

35
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:12,040
If we don't kill them, they'll kill us.

36
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:17,560
If you're this soft, maybe
you shouldn't be fighting.

37
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:20,399
Comrade Fah.

38
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,560
It's Comrade Saeng's
first time in the battle.

39
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:27,639
Keep indulging him like this,

40
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:29,120
and we'd all be damed.

41
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:36,840
Learn how to sympathize
for once, Comrade Fah.

42
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:40,480
Not everything revolves around you.

43
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:04,359
I want to visit Yaguar's mother.

44
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,240
Wanna come with?

45
00:04:05,241 --> 00:04:07,199
Comrade Roong, heading back?

46
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:08,200
I'll go too.

47
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:10,359
I need to finish writing my article.

48
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:11,360
Go ahead.

49
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:19,439
Hey, Sila.

50
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:20,600
Let me ask you something.

51
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,679
Do you still see Mada as your girlfriend?

52
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:26,080
You've been acting
distant lately—like strangers.

53
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:29,479
We came here for a cause.

54
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:32,159
Ideals come first—love comes later.

55
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:33,599
Don't you remember?

56
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,599
If you keep acting like this,

57
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:37,520
how are you going to achieve anything?

58
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:55,760
Wow.

59
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:58,800
I didn't know we had a place
this beautiful here, Bai Tong.

60
00:04:58,960 --> 00:04:59,960
Yeah.

61
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,279
This is one of our secret bases.

62
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:06,360
Only trusted people are allowed in.

63
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,840
Comrade Bai Tong, Comrade Saeng.

64
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:21,879
This is a reward for your victory,

65
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:24,400
and for bringing everyone back safely.

66
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:28,120
You did great, Comrade Saeng.

67
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:32,080
Comrade Bai Tong.

68
00:05:32,081 --> 00:05:33,239
Hmm?

69
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:35,360
Can I ask for one more?

70
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:37,760
Cause I…

71
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:40,280
I want to give it to…

72
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:45,240
someone… a friend.

73
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:47,639
You can take a whole bunch if you want.

74
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:48,840
Come on, let's pick some.

75
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:50,320
Yeah.

76
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,759
Come with us, Comrade Saeng.

77
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:53,640
If you're giving it to someone,

78
00:05:53,641 --> 00:05:54,841
you should choose it yourself.

79
00:06:05,880 --> 00:06:07,240
Are you in there, Comrade Yue?

80
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:17,440
Yeah?

81
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:29,840
This is for you.

82
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:45,800
Thanks for taking care of me.

83
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,879
Why are you giving this to me?

84
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:55,080
If you do something
good, you deserve a reward.

85
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:01,080
Do you know what a cockscomb flower means?

86
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:06,240
Cockscomb flower? It has a meaning?

87
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:09,039
I'm not sure either.

88
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:11,240
But Comrade Bai Tong gave it to me.

89
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:20,279
Among the Hmong,

90
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:21,800
they give cockscomb flowers to-

91
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,640
someone they're interested in.

92
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:30,200
It means.

93
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:32,560
“I want to get to know you,”

94
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:37,240
“I want to talk to you.”

95
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:47,320
Now that you know…

96
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:49,880
Want to have it back?

97
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,440
I gave it to you.

98
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:57,320
I'm not taking it back.

99
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,040
Comrade Yue!

100
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:28,400
Comrade Yue!

101
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:31,200
Comrade Yue!

102
00:08:31,201 --> 00:08:32,239
Yeah?

103
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:35,199
What's going on? Everyone
else is about to collapse.

104
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,440
Can we take a break?

105
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:37,960
That's it.

106
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:48,160
What are you looking at, Comrade Phu Pha?

107
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:50,000
What's wrong with you?

108
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:51,680
Huh?

109
00:08:51,703 --> 00:08:54,223
You look like your soul's
still stuck on the battlefield.

110
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:57,959
Oh…

111
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:59,559
If something's on your mind, just say it.

112
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:00,880
Why keep it bottled up?

113
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:04,359
Ugh… sooner or later, I'm
going to find out anyway.

114
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:05,360
Just spill it.

115
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:06,920
Come on.

116
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:25,120
If you've got feelings for someone…

117
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:29,520
but you know it shouldn't happen,

118
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,760
what would you do?

119
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:34,880
Don't tell me—you've fallen for someone?

120
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:37,920
Hold on, man.

121
00:09:39,206 --> 00:09:41,446
If you think it's real, then go for it.

122
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:44,400
What, are you scared of
the Three Delays Policy?

123
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:47,560
That policy doesn't apply to love, does it?

124
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:50,480
I know right.

125
00:09:50,481 --> 00:09:53,000
But it's not that simple.

126
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:57,120
I think If you're honest
with your feelings,

127
00:09:57,880 --> 00:09:59,400
then nothing's really that hard.

128
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:03,879
We're living in a battlefield.

129
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:05,680
We could die any day.

130
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:09,559
So if you still have the
strength to love someone,

131
00:10:09,560 --> 00:10:11,439
then just love them.

132
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:12,840
Don't overthink it.

133
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:16,800
Come on—

134
00:10:18,760 --> 00:10:19,760
go confess.

135
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:02,199
Among the Hmong,

136
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:04,719
they give a cockscomb flower

137
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:06,200
to someone they're interested in.

138
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:09,160
It means.

139
00:11:10,640 --> 00:11:11,760
“I want to get to know you,”

140
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:13,840
“I want to talk to you.”

141
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:18,440
Now that you know…

142
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:21,120
want to have it back?

143
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:25,680
I gave it to you.

144
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:27,440
I'm not taking it back.

145
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:31,080
Hey!!

146
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:33,880
What the fuck is with that smile?
Creepy motherfucker.

147
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:40,999
(Music playing)
As the sunlight slowly fades away,

148
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:44,999
all I need is someone by my side.

149
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:49,399
Let it be you, let it be you.

150
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:53,239
Just sitting close, meeting
your eyes, warms my heart.

151
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:56,999
Let this moment be just the two of us.

152
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:01,079
Like the moon waiting
for its time to shine.

153
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:05,039
Let it be you, can it be you?

154
00:13:05,040 --> 00:13:09,119
The one who stays by
my side and never leaves.

155
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:13,440
Let it be you…

156
00:13:33,640 --> 00:13:36,960
This clearing just never seems
to end in a large field here.

157
00:13:37,640 --> 00:13:39,720
I still haven't finished
writing my article.

158
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:43,160
Every time we clear it, you complain.

159
00:13:44,680 --> 00:13:47,040
Work like this should
be shared across all units.

160
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:49,520
Even the villagers are helping out.

161
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:57,040
Labor is honor.

162
00:13:58,240 --> 00:14:00,200
Did you forget what the Party taught us?

163
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:18,040
Comrade…

164
00:14:18,041 --> 00:14:20,399
Did you do something to upset Comrade Yue?

165
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:21,479
He keeps staring at you.

166
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:22,920
No—nothing.

167
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:25,160
Not at all.

168
00:14:25,520 --> 00:14:27,000
Why are you getting all high-pitched?

169
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:28,600
That's suspicious.

170
00:14:29,280 --> 00:14:30,280
Suspicious?

171
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:37,960
Hey!!

172
00:14:37,961 --> 00:14:40,519
Sorry—my bad, slipped a bit.

173
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:41,520
Hey,

174
00:14:42,560 --> 00:14:43,560
are you okay?

175
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:44,640
Huh?

176
00:14:44,641 --> 00:14:45,760
You're bleeding.

177
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:50,200
Oh—

178
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:51,800
it's nothing.

179
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:54,320
Be more careful.

180
00:14:59,640 --> 00:15:01,519
Thank you, everyone,

181
00:15:01,520 --> 00:15:04,199
for working together like this.

182
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,719
Preparing the soil
for this year's crops is-

183
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:07,960
-something we all share responsibility for.

184
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:13,840
Here, no matter your rank or position,

185
00:15:14,920 --> 00:15:16,920
everyone is equal.

186
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:20,600
We work just as hard,

187
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:23,880
so the rewards-

188
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:25,760
-must be equal too.

189
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:29,800
Thank you.

190
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:34,520
So the harvest from this year

191
00:15:35,560 --> 00:15:38,600
will be shared by
everyone, just like before.

192
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:37,600
Is it good?

193
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:39,680
I haven't tried it yet.

194
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:55,440
What's wrong, Comrade Ying? You look pale.

195
00:16:58,160 --> 00:16:59,800
Just a stomachache.

196
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:03,199
Is it your period? Want
me to get you medicine?

197
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,839
I'll find some for you.

198
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:07,039
You're really bringing
this up while we're eating?

199
00:17:07,040 --> 00:17:08,560
You're gonna ruin everyone's appetite.

200
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:12,199
Period pain is no different
from a headache or a fever.

201
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:13,640
What's so disgusting about it?

202
00:17:16,560 --> 00:17:18,399
Are you okay?

203
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:20,240
Do you get this every month?

204
00:17:22,160 --> 00:17:23,960
My period hasn't come
for five or six months.

205
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:25,480
Five or six months!?

206
00:17:26,753 --> 00:17:28,113
Maybe you should see a doctor.

207
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:30,920
How does it not come for that long?

208
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:33,360
You're not taking care of yourself.

209
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:35,240
Why are you scolding me?

210
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:37,559
Because I care.

211
00:17:37,560 --> 00:17:38,720
If this is how you care,

212
00:17:39,320 --> 00:17:40,840
then don't.

213
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,400
What's going on here?

214
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:53,159
We may have raised our voices,

215
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:55,599
but we're not fighting or causing trouble.

216
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:57,599
Loud but not fighting?

217
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:59,280
Who's going to believe that?

218
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:02,800
Everyone here saw you two arguing.

219
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:07,840
This is exactly why the
Three Delays policy exists.

220
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:10,240
Love only causes problems.

221
00:18:10,793 --> 00:18:12,753
When people fall out,
they can't work together.

222
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:16,279
If you'd just let the
two of them talk it out,

223
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:17,759
it would've been over already.

224
00:18:17,760 --> 00:18:21,000
Instead, outsiders turn
small issues into big ones.

225
00:18:24,360 --> 00:18:26,359
That loud argument still
wasn't big enough for you?

226
00:18:26,360 --> 00:18:28,440
You know fighting isn't allowed here.

227
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:31,719
This needs to be punished, Comrade Ploeng.

228
00:18:31,720 --> 00:18:33,639
So others don't follow this example.

229
00:18:33,640 --> 00:18:36,319
I think you two should
stop doing mass work.

230
00:18:36,320 --> 00:18:38,560
You'd be better off farming instead.

231
00:18:39,577 --> 00:18:42,576
No, sir—I'm better suited for mass work.

232
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:44,680
I still have many articles to write.

233
00:18:47,240 --> 00:18:51,119
Comrade Fah, what are you
basing your judgment on?

234
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:52,799
This is our first offense.

235
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:54,719
We've never done anything wrong before.

236
00:18:54,720 --> 00:18:56,600
A warning should be enough.

237
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:01,160
Alright alright alright,

238
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:03,480
that's enough.

239
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:10,079
This is your first time
causing a disturbance.

240
00:19:10,080 --> 00:19:11,759
I won't punish you.

241
00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:13,440
But if it happens again,

242
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:16,200
it won't just be a warning.

243
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:20,360
Alright, dismissed.

244
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:27,360
Hey!

245
00:19:50,640 --> 00:19:52,200
You little troublemaker.

246
00:19:53,080 --> 00:19:54,200
What, Comrade Yue?

247
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:55,760
What troublemaker?

248
00:19:57,280 --> 00:19:58,439
Oh—

249
00:19:58,440 --> 00:20:00,840
the wound. It troubles me.

250
00:20:08,920 --> 00:20:12,280
Comrade Ying! Comrade Ying! Comrade Ying!

251
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:14,480
Let go of me.

252
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:17,480
I'm sorry…

253
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:20,200
for raising my voice at you earlier.

254
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:22,959
It's just that you don't
take care of yourself.

255
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:24,720
I can't help but worry.

256
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:28,400
It's messing with my focus at work.

257
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:31,440
You should try to understand me too.

258
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:35,160
Yes,

259
00:20:35,560 --> 00:20:37,240
we should prioritize work and ideology.

260
00:20:38,040 --> 00:20:39,200
Love comes second.

261
00:20:41,146 --> 00:20:42,786
Then let's make it clear.

262
00:20:43,520 --> 00:20:45,920
We already disagree on
so many things anyway.

263
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:50,920
What do you mean?

264
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:01,239
Let's break up.

265
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:03,160
Hey—what the hell?

266
00:21:37,360 --> 00:21:38,600
Haha!

267
00:21:41,040 --> 00:21:42,320
Hahahaha.

268
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:46,480
I am the god of cockscomb flowers!

269
00:21:47,320 --> 00:21:50,679
Today, I grant Comrade Ying one wish!

270
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:55,520
You get one wish.

271
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:07,319
- Come on, Comrade Ying.
- Hurry up!

272
00:22:07,320 --> 00:22:08,879
I'm getting tired here.

273
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:11,520
So tired—help me!

274
00:22:18,160 --> 00:22:20,000
I wish that the person I love-

275
00:22:21,560 --> 00:22:23,119
-will never make me cry again.

276
00:22:23,120 --> 00:22:26,119
Ah hahaha.

277
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:32,400
Then I grant your wish. May it come true.

278
00:22:33,720 --> 00:22:36,520
Alright, stop crying—get up.

279
00:22:37,720 --> 00:22:39,239
Come on, up you go.

280
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:41,440
Let's dance.

281
00:24:07,960 --> 00:24:09,280
What's wrong with you?

282
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:11,200
I'm fine.

283
00:24:12,280 --> 00:24:14,440
You're the one who's not.

284
00:24:15,360 --> 00:24:16,360
Huh?

285
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:19,360
Right here.

286
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:26,760
Oh—it's nothing. It'll heal.

287
00:24:27,920 --> 00:24:30,360
That's exactly why I want to treat it.

288
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:35,960
You don't need to.

289
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:06,280
Just knowing you care is enough.

290
00:25:17,760 --> 00:25:19,240
Does it still hurt?

291
00:25:22,840 --> 00:25:25,600
Ouch—yeah, it hurts.

292
00:25:26,480 --> 00:25:27,800
Still hurts?

293
00:25:39,560 --> 00:25:40,600
Comrade Roong!

294
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:44,800
Comrade Roong!

295
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:49,639
Is Comrade Roong not here?

296
00:25:49,640 --> 00:25:50,920
Comrade Ploeng called a meeting.

297
00:25:53,880 --> 00:25:55,040
Oh,

298
00:25:57,200 --> 00:25:59,200
they went to the villagers' area.

299
00:26:00,833 --> 00:26:03,353
Comrade Yue too. Comrade Ploeng is waiting.

300
00:26:04,120 --> 00:26:05,120
Oh.

301
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:32,400
Don't forget to apply the medicine.

302
00:26:43,760 --> 00:26:45,519
Comrade, move the stuff to the platform.

303
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:46,520
Okay.

304
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:53,520
Careful.

305
00:26:56,320 --> 00:26:58,279
There are more weapons
this time than usual.

306
00:26:58,280 --> 00:26:59,760
Are we preparing for a big operation?

307
00:27:00,240 --> 00:27:01,800
Uh… where?

308
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:04,719
Why are you asking?

309
00:27:04,720 --> 00:27:06,320
You're usually not interested in combat.

310
00:27:06,960 --> 00:27:07,960
- Um...
- Yaguar,

311
00:27:08,560 --> 00:27:09,840
come help carry this crate.

312
00:27:20,920 --> 00:27:22,960
Achoo! Achoo!

313
00:27:23,697 --> 00:27:25,216
Allergies are acting up again, aren't they?

314
00:27:25,240 --> 00:27:27,159
How are you going to fight like that?

315
00:27:27,160 --> 00:27:28,399
I'm not going.

316
00:27:28,400 --> 00:27:30,120
Comrade Ploeng told me to stay at the base.

317
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:35,320
Then sit down and rest.

318
00:27:36,560 --> 00:27:38,080
It's fine—there are plenty of people.

319
00:27:48,880 --> 00:27:49,880
You don't look well—

320
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:51,760
you've been sneezing nonstop.

321
00:27:57,280 --> 00:27:58,760
I'll roll you some herbal cigarettes.

322
00:27:59,880 --> 00:28:01,280
I don't smoke.

323
00:28:02,480 --> 00:28:04,560
Mine help with allergies.

324
00:28:09,346 --> 00:28:12,106
Since when did you care about me?

325
00:28:19,560 --> 00:28:21,200
Do I look like I don't?

326
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:27,480
Has anyone seen Comrade Bai Tong?

327
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:32,360
I heard Comrade Ploeng is taking her
for shooting practice.

328
00:28:33,040 --> 00:28:34,040
Is something wrong?

329
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:37,519
Then can you check over there?

330
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:39,320
Looks like the supply
delivery is incomplete.

331
00:28:56,520 --> 00:29:00,759
One more time—steady
hands, raise your shoulders.

332
00:29:00,760 --> 00:29:02,239
Grip tight.

333
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:03,240
Ready…

334
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:05,600
Go.

335
00:29:05,760 --> 00:29:06,800
Yay!

336
00:29:07,640 --> 00:29:08,520
Yay!

337
00:29:08,521 --> 00:29:10,199
Yay! This is fun, Dad!

338
00:29:10,200 --> 00:29:15,160
Good job—that's my girl!

339
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:17,800
Remember this—.

340
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:20,000
I'm not training you-

341
00:29:20,840 --> 00:29:22,200
-just for fun.

342
00:29:22,920 --> 00:29:25,960
You need to learn to protect yourself
in case I'm not around.

343
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:28,399
So you can take care of yourself.

344
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:29,520
Do you understand?

345
00:29:30,160 --> 00:29:33,280
Do you have to go fight
again? Can't you stay?

346
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:41,440
My girl,

347
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:43,720
you're already well aware

348
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:47,720
that I have a duty,
just like everyone else,

349
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:50,720
to protect this base so
everyone here can live safely.

350
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:54,119
Comrade Ying told me

351
00:29:54,120 --> 00:29:56,360
that people outside don't
have to carry guns and fight.

352
00:29:57,440 --> 00:29:59,120
Cause if we win,

353
00:30:00,520 --> 00:30:02,920
then we won't have to carry guns anymore.

354
00:30:04,320 --> 00:30:08,600
No matter where we are,
we won't have to fight again.

355
00:30:10,200 --> 00:30:12,960
You'll get to live like a normal child.

356
00:30:13,760 --> 00:30:15,960
I want to see what the
outside world is like.

357
00:30:16,560 --> 00:30:19,320
Please bring victory
and take me there, dad.

358
00:30:24,600 --> 00:30:26,160
That's a deal, my girl.

359
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:44,200
Yaguar.

360
00:30:50,240 --> 00:30:51,240
Here—.

361
00:30:51,600 --> 00:30:53,560
Comrade Roong asked me
to give you this medicine.

362
00:30:54,440 --> 00:30:55,440
Thank you.

363
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:07,400
She's already requested more from HQ.

364
00:31:09,560 --> 00:31:10,560
Hang in there for now.

365
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:13,760
You like him that much, huh?

366
00:31:14,280 --> 00:31:15,959
Is that why you broke up with me?

367
00:31:15,960 --> 00:31:16,560
Comrade Gaun Hin.

368
00:31:16,561 --> 00:31:17,839
- You like him that much?
- Comrade Gaun Hin.

369
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:19,119
What does he have that I don't?!

370
00:31:19,120 --> 00:31:20,120
Sila.

371
00:31:20,560 --> 00:31:21,720
That's enough, Sila. Stop it.

372
00:31:24,920 --> 00:31:26,159
You like him that much, huh?!

373
00:31:26,160 --> 00:31:27,839
Comrade Ying just brought me medicine.

374
00:31:27,840 --> 00:31:28,840
Don't get the wrong idea.

375
00:31:29,320 --> 00:31:30,280
Do you know-

376
00:31:30,281 --> 00:31:32,599
-how much she cried because of you?

377
00:31:32,600 --> 00:31:33,840
It took her so long to stop.

378
00:31:36,793 --> 00:31:38,793
Please don't hurt her again.

379
00:31:40,240 --> 00:31:41,240
Yaguar.

380
00:31:43,160 --> 00:31:44,600
Go take the medicine to your mother.

381
00:32:18,120 --> 00:32:19,519
What are you going to do
with those 'Cork tree' flowers,

382
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:20,520
Comrade Yue?

383
00:32:21,920 --> 00:32:23,240
Comrade Saeng has allergies.

384
00:32:32,560 --> 00:32:34,376
His nose has turned red
from sneezing non-stop.

385
00:32:34,400 --> 00:32:37,040
If he's not feeling well,
just get him medicine.

386
00:32:37,960 --> 00:32:39,520
Why do you even have to do all this?

387
00:32:40,840 --> 00:32:42,160
I want to do it myself.

388
00:32:45,720 --> 00:32:48,159
It's on your neck like this and if you can
still lose it, I'll be speechless.

389
00:32:48,160 --> 00:32:49,680
Not losing it anymore.

390
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:52,200
Then let me help.

391
00:32:53,160 --> 00:32:54,520
It's okay, Comrade Roong.

392
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:57,200
You've been taking
care of patients all day.

393
00:33:01,080 --> 00:33:02,080
Go get some rest.

394
00:33:04,960 --> 00:33:06,879
Hey, what are you waiting for?

395
00:33:06,880 --> 00:33:09,439
I'll catch up. You two go ahead.
I'm not that hungry yet.

396
00:33:09,440 --> 00:33:11,080
Alright.

397
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:22,640
That should do.

398
00:33:56,840 --> 00:33:58,240
Where are you wandering off to?

399
00:34:08,280 --> 00:34:10,719
The day we transported weapons,

400
00:34:10,720 --> 00:34:12,480
I noticed Yagaur acting strange.

401
00:34:13,960 --> 00:34:15,560
Ask Comrade Roong to keep an eye on him.

402
00:34:20,240 --> 00:34:22,000
And what about you and Comrade Yue?

403
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:27,040
I saw you two talking for a while earlier.

404
00:34:32,200 --> 00:34:33,520
Well,

405
00:34:35,880 --> 00:34:37,280
It's nothing.

406
00:34:44,080 --> 00:34:45,560
You still like him, don't you?

407
00:34:51,480 --> 00:34:53,239
It's been years already.

408
00:34:53,240 --> 00:34:54,399
You should know by now—

409
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:56,160
he only sees you as a younger sister.

410
00:35:00,360 --> 00:35:02,600
If he liked you, he
would've shown it by now.

411
00:35:04,800 --> 00:35:06,440
I'm saying this because I care about you.

412
00:35:07,320 --> 00:35:08,920
I don't want to see you get hurt again.

413
00:35:14,960 --> 00:35:17,319
If that's all you had to say,

414
00:35:17,320 --> 00:35:19,720
I'll get back to work.

415
00:35:34,639 --> 00:35:35,639
Have you figured it out?

416
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:38,800
Why HQ sent weapons to Baan Saeng Dao base?

417
00:35:41,600 --> 00:35:44,760
Comrade Ploeng is preparing to
seize a military stronghold.

418
00:35:47,120 --> 00:35:48,120
Which one?

419
00:35:50,320 --> 00:35:51,320
It's...

420
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:54,079
the closest base.

421
00:35:54,080 --> 00:35:55,160
Right…

422
00:35:58,080 --> 00:35:59,120
By the way,

423
00:36:00,880 --> 00:36:02,360
do you know the person in this photo?

424
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:09,240
That's Comrade Saeng.

425
00:36:10,680 --> 00:36:13,479
You know him too? Which base is he at?

426
00:36:13,480 --> 00:36:14,720
He's with Baan Saeng Dao base.

427
00:36:15,520 --> 00:36:18,063
He's the one who took down the
commander of Baan Prongdong.

428
00:36:24,800 --> 00:36:27,000
Is something wrong?

429
00:36:33,240 --> 00:36:34,440
In a few days,

430
00:36:35,120 --> 00:36:38,000
I'll have someone take your mother
to a hospital in the city.

431
00:36:39,800 --> 00:36:41,840
Don't worry—I'll handle everything.

432
00:36:42,840 --> 00:36:45,039
Just find out what I asked for—

433
00:36:45,040 --> 00:36:46,720
and everything about Comrade Saeng.

434
00:36:48,760 --> 00:36:50,480
Tell me everything you know.

435
00:37:19,960 --> 00:37:21,000
Why did you call me here?

436
00:37:26,040 --> 00:37:28,000
Hey—hey—!

437
00:37:30,360 --> 00:37:32,160
You'll alert the whole base at this rate.

438
00:37:34,560 --> 00:37:36,920
Sneaking up on me like that scared me.

439
00:37:37,800 --> 00:37:39,160
You're the one who called me here.

440
00:37:39,400 --> 00:37:41,840
Or not? I'll head back then.

441
00:37:44,320 --> 00:37:45,320
Come with me.

442
00:38:05,120 --> 00:38:06,160
If you wanted to stargaze,

443
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:08,280
why not ask Comrade Roong?

444
00:38:09,280 --> 00:38:10,400
Why me?

445
00:38:11,960 --> 00:38:13,520
I didn't want to stargaze.

446
00:38:15,520 --> 00:38:18,240
And even if I did, it wouldn't
be with Comrade Roong.

447
00:38:47,640 --> 00:38:50,600
What's that smell? It's nice.

448
00:38:51,760 --> 00:38:54,840
Cork tree' flower
cigarettes—they help with allergies.

449
00:38:56,880 --> 00:38:58,079
Try it.

450
00:38:58,080 --> 00:38:59,479
I don't smoke.

451
00:38:59,480 --> 00:39:01,600
Just try—I'll show you.

452
00:39:06,920 --> 00:39:07,920
Inhale.

453
00:39:11,360 --> 00:39:12,360
A bit deeper.

454
00:39:16,920 --> 00:39:18,320
How is it?

455
00:39:19,360 --> 00:39:22,120
It's nice… smells good.

456
00:39:24,600 --> 00:39:26,959
Ew—why didn't you roll a new one?

457
00:39:26,960 --> 00:39:30,200
This one has my saliva on it. Make another.

458
00:39:37,280 --> 00:39:38,440
Beautiful stars, aren't they?

459
00:39:39,920 --> 00:39:41,480
So who did you roll that for?

460
00:39:48,160 --> 00:39:51,360
Even though we're at
base, I can't show it openly.

461
00:39:52,920 --> 00:39:54,680
But that doesn't mean
I don't feel anything.

462
00:39:59,640 --> 00:40:00,800
Feel what?

463
00:40:05,720 --> 00:40:08,200
That you're very special to me.

464
00:40:11,880 --> 00:40:13,400
And I want to take care of you.

465
00:40:21,120 --> 00:40:22,120
Not mad anymore?

466
00:40:24,960 --> 00:40:25,960
Ahh.

467
00:40:26,920 --> 00:40:29,200
I wasn't mad to begin with.

468
00:40:32,960 --> 00:40:33,960
Look at my cigarette?

469
00:40:34,737 --> 00:40:37,096
There's still half left, and
you kicked it away—

470
00:40:37,120 --> 00:40:38,360
I worked hard rolling that one.

471
00:40:40,200 --> 00:40:42,240
Forget it… The stars…
let's just watch the stars.

472
00:40:52,260 --> 00:40:54,295
(Comrades, victory belongs to the people.)

473
00:40:54,340 --> 00:40:58,800
This time, we fight 'til
the end. They have guns,

474
00:40:59,640 --> 00:41:01,519
we have guns.

475
00:41:01,520 --> 00:41:04,160
And we will never bow to anyone.

476
00:41:05,640 --> 00:41:06,880
If we fight,

477
00:41:07,920 --> 00:41:09,839
we fight together.

478
00:41:09,840 --> 00:41:11,320
And if we die,

479
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:15,800
I will die beside all of you—my comrades.

480
00:41:17,240 --> 00:41:21,319
And this time, we will return with victory.

481
00:41:21,320 --> 00:41:26,719
And we'll celebrate that
victory on our Party's anniversary.

482
00:41:26,720 --> 00:41:28,759
Yes, sir—I'm already
preparing the celebration.

483
00:41:28,760 --> 00:41:31,120
Yay!

484
00:41:32,200 --> 00:41:33,559
I'll be a good girl.

485
00:41:33,560 --> 00:41:35,600
I won't be naughty. Come back soon, Dad.

486
00:41:36,600 --> 00:41:38,960
Good girl. I love you.

487
00:41:55,400 --> 00:41:58,080
Comrades, are you ready?

488
00:41:58,480 --> 00:41:59,480
Ready!

489
00:42:00,640 --> 00:42:01,400
Will we fight?
Fight!

490
00:42:05,640 --> 00:42:06,640
Fight!

491
00:42:18,120 --> 00:42:19,999
Let's do this!

492
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:26,880
Fight! Fight!

493
00:42:58,920 --> 00:42:59,720
Go!

494
00:42:59,721 --> 00:43:01,080
Comrades. Go!

495
00:43:04,560 --> 00:43:06,200
Their base is ours tonight!
